  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Empowering local community structures to respond to and  mitigate child rights violations in Kismayo</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will ensure that timely response services are in place for children whose rights have been violated. The project will established a counselling centre to support children whose rights have been violated. The Center will be equipped with the necessary supplies and staff will be trained on Child protection. A community support mechanism to facilitate referrals of child violated cases will be strengthened and concrete training of the service provision points will be conducted to ensure that children access services without any harm. The project will also ensure that un accompanied children and separated children are identified and reunited with their families. Community structures such as the child protection committees and water user committees will be strengthened to ensure that they participate in mitigation of child abuse initiatives. Boys and girls will be trained to adopt safe risk mitigation strategies.</narrative>
  </description>
